IN CASE OF EMERGENCY LANDING please follow these instructions:
1. Put out lighted cigarette, loosen tie and collar, and remove shoes and eye glasses.
2. Take fountain pens and any pointed objects out of your pockets.
3. Move the seat to the upright position. Put a folded blanket over your abdomen and fasten your seat
belt. Sit in the position shown in the drawing and re.nain in your seat in this position until the plane
comes to a stop after landing.
4. After the plane stops, leave by the door or emergency exit nearest you.
